This paper is about language modeling using neural network sequence models, which falls under the category of natural language processing (NLP). Therefore, cs.CL (Computation and Language) is the most likely sub-category. The paper also introduces a new architecture for neural sequence models, which could be of interest to researchers in machine learning (cs.LG), artificial intelligence (cs.AI), and neural networks (cs.NE). Additionally, the paper mentions using the WikiText corpus, which could be relevant to researchers in computer vision (cs.CV) who work with large datasets.
